Project description: Sites for a snapshot test. Differing depths and observations
Selected soil description: The Ketchum series consists of very deep, well drained soils that formed in colluvium from limestone, quartzitic sandstone and related rock. Ketchum soils are on mountains and have slopes of 20 to 75 percent. Permeability is moderately rapid.  The mean annual precipitation is about 510 mm, and the mean annual air temperature is about 3 degrees C.
